        "text": "A recruiter reached out to me about this opportunity on LinkedIn. Just passing the opportunity along for anyone who might be interested. Email Jenny Chen (*<mailto:jenny.chen@hireio.us|jenny.chen@hireio.us>*) if you’re interested.\n\n_The company is an AI-powered news aggregator that delivers the most relevant local news to users. They are ahead of major news outlets and platforms such as The New York Times, CNN News, The Washington Post, Yahoo News, and SmartNews on mobile._ \n\n_They are seeking an experienced Content Operations Manager to help drive operational excellence across the content that powers all of the suite, including: content strategy &amp; programming on our core app, push notification operations, newsletter content, as well as other consumer-facing content channels such as social networks, blog\/company websites, and marketing campaigns on various channels. This role will create, build and own the operational processes around the company’s content management across all channels. The Content Operations role will be instrumental in ensuring that the content they creates is maintained, managed and syndicated._\n\n*Location*\n• Mountain View \n• Permanent position \n• No Visa Sponsorship \n*Responsibilities* \n• Oversee the content programming strategy on our core mobile app \n• Manage editorial-based push notification operations \n• Identify gaps in our content and recommend new topics \n• Design, run, and evaluate content marketing campaigns on various channels \n• Create style guides to use as reference \n• Proofread and edit written pieces before publication \n• Monitor web traffic and engagement (e.g. conversions and bounce rates) \n• Coordinate with marketing and design teams to illustrate articles \n• Follow industry-related news and generate ideas around trending topics \n*Requirements* \n• BSc in Marketing, Journalism or a relevant field \n• Proven work experience as a Content Strategist, Content Operations or similar role \n• A portfolio of published articles \n• Knowledge of Content Management Systems, like WordPress Basic understanding of HTML and web publishing \n• Familiarity with SEO guidelines and keyword research tools (e.g. Moz and Google Keyword Planner) \n• Solid writing and editing skills in English \n• Time-management skills \n• Ability to guide and motivate team members \n• Experience in creator network management is a big plus \n• Experience in publisher management Experience in project management",
